Netcat:

nc -nv : connect to TCP port
nc -lvp : listening on a given TCP port
nc -lvp 1234 > output.txt or nc -lvp <IP> < output.txt  : trasfer a file
nc -nv <IP> 80 GET / HTTP/1.1 : connecting and receiving a webpage (Port 443 for https)
nc -z <IP> <port range> : port scanning

