PowerSploit is a collection of PowerShell modules that can be used for post-exploitation and other phases of an assessment. 

Empire, which is an open-source framework that includes a PowerShell Windows agent and a Python Linux agent. Empire implements the ability to run PowerShell agents without the need for powershell.exe. 

BloodHound that uses graph theory to reveal the hidden relationships in a Windows Active Directory environment.You can also use BloodHound to find complex attack paths in Microsoft Azure.
BloodHound is a JavaScript web application that uses graph theory to reveal the hidden relationships in a Windows Active Directory environment. An attacker can use BloodHound to identify numerous attack paths. 
Similarly, incident response teams can use BloodHound to detect and eliminate those same attack paths.

Sysinternals is a suite of tools that allows administrators to control Windows-based computers from a remote terminal.
PsExec is one of the most powerful Sysinternals tools. You can use it to remotely execute anything that can run on a Windows command prompt. 

